comment: O'Bryant (MIL) legally contests Hickson's (DEN) layup attempt. Any contact that occurs is incidental and after the ball has been released.
[Observable in enhanced video] Bayless (MIL) switches his pivot foot before releasing the pass.
Hickson (DEN) sets the screen on Bayless (MIL) without giving him the room to avoid the contact.
Faried (DEN) affects Monroe's (MIL) FOM as he cuts away from the ball.

Bayless (MIL) has little contact with Mudiay (DEN), who trips on Faried (DEN). CC was on Faried, who is not in a legal screening position when Bayless hits his leg. If a player uses a wide screen stance, contact must be absorbed in his upper body.
Monroe (MIL) sets the screen on Gallinari (DEN) and gives him the room to avoid the contact.
O'Bryant (MIL) makes contact with Mudiay's (DEN) arm that affects his drive to the basket and layup attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Gallinari (DEN) makes incidental contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL) away from the ball.

Faried (DEN) jumps vertically and legally contests Antetokounmpo's (MIL) driving layup attempt. NOTE: Due to technical issues, video of plays may be unavailable or not matched to the correct time code. We apologize for any inconvenience and will post an update after the issue is resolved.
